{"first_name":"Steve","last_name":"Markowitz","permalink":"steve-markowitz","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/steve-markowitz","homepage_url":"http://www.SteveMarkowitz.com","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"TransactionTree","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Sat Feb 02 07:24:17 UTC 2008","updated_at":"Wed Sep 05 05:55:27 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Steve Markowitz is an investor and entrepreneur, whose experience includes leading a successful IPO.</p>\n\n<p>AngelList has recognized Steve as a &#8220;notable founder&#8221; and &#8220;notable operator.&#8221;</p>\n\n<p>Steve is co-founder and seed investor of BeeStripe, Mile High Organics and NetPlenish.  Also, he is a founding investor in and board member of Ritter Pharmaceuticals.</p>\n\n<p>Previously, Steve was co-founder, former chairman and CEO of pioneering loyalty marketer MyPoints.com. He led the company from inception as Intellipost Corp. in Nov. 1996 through its successful $46 million IPO (Aug. 1999), $211 million secondary offering (Feb. 2000) and beyond.  Under Steve&#8217;s stewardship, MyPoints.com grew to a peak market value of approximately $1.4 billion.</p>\n\n<p>Steve&#8217;s early career includes experience as a securities analyst for Fidelity Investments and as a financial journalist for Dow Jones &amp; Co., both in Tokyo. He is fluent in Japanese. </p>\n\n<p>Steve holds two degrees from UC Berkeley, an MBA and a B.A. in East Asian Languages (high honors, Japanese).  He has been honored by UC Berkeley&#8217;s Haas School of Business with the coveted Richard H. Holton Teaching Fellowship (2009), recognizing his well-received lectures in the Entrepreneurship and New Venture Finance courses.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[80,78],"assets/images/resized/0001/8741/18741v1-max-150x150.png"],[[80,78],"assets/images/resized/0001/8741/18741v1-max-250x250.png"],[[80,78],"as